Second point, when balancing spells you don't factor in AA too.  AA was balanced against AA, each class has their own and it was factored into over-all class balance when it was created.  If you start saying &quot;well add 20% crit rate to all Wiz nukes when comparing them vs. Mage&quot; are you going to also say &quot;well factor in Mage ability to canni pets when comparing spell ratios&quot;?  No, I didn't think so.  The &quot;well class X gets AA ability Y&quot; argument only comes up for a class to justify a spell change that doesn't make sense.  I could just as easily say that all 54+ Mage spells should be considered with a +10% damage value on them, since Mage can self-buff with a Damage Focus item, while Wizards can't create one of their own.  Oh, well then you would want to say &quot;well Wizards can wear damage foci too!&quot;  You can keep tossing equipment and abilities on each side of the scale, tilting it back and forth depending on who's side you stack the most stuff on.  The point it to compare spell for spell and treat items, buffs, AAs, etc as separate cases to be balanced against each other. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uelasto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(10/18/02 12:15:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: don't insult people's intelligence!</span><hr size=1> This is why I call this friction *needless*. Cos it is meaningless and unnescessary.<br>
